Peru Stocks: Cerro Verde, Credicorp, Maple, Minsur Advance

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-08-11T21:19:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/peru-stocks-cerro-verde-credicorp-maple-minsur-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:44 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 3.7 percent to 19,678.72. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 3.9 percent to 2,505.21.  Mining and energy companies advanced as copper and crude
oil rose after a drop in U.S. jobless claims tempered concern
the economy is slowing.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, jumped the most in nine weeks, rising 9.3 percent to
3.30 soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), Peru’s
third-largest copper producer, advanced for the second time in
10 sessions, gaining 6.8 percent to $39.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO) 
, the nation’s biggest copper producer, climbed 5.8
percent to a one-week high of $31.20.  Empresa Siderurgica del
Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Brazilian steelmaker Gerdau SA,
rose 5.8 percent to 1.27 soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the
oil and natural gas producer with operations in Peru, rose 5
percent to $1.05.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
holding company, advanced the most in three weeks after second-
quarter earnings rose 7.6 percent from a year earlier. The Lima-
based company added 3.4 percent to $87.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
